{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I told you three things last year."},{"time":2000,"text":"I told you that the statistics of the world"},{"time":5000,"text":"have not been made properly available."},{"time":8000,"text":"Because of that, we still have the old mindset"},{"time":10000,"text":"of developing in industrialized countries, which is wrong."},{"time":14000,"text":"And that animated graphics can make a difference."},{"time":19000,"text":"Things are changing"},{"time":21000,"text":"and today, on the United Nations Statistic Division Home Page,"},{"time":25000,"text":"it says, by first of May, full access to the databases."},{"time":30000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":33000,"text":"And if I could share the image with you on the screen."},{"time":38000,"text":"So three things have happened."},{"time":39000,"text":"U.N. opened their statistic databases,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and we have a new version of the software"},{"time":46000,"text":"up working as a beta on the net,"},{"time":48000,"text":"so you don't have to download it any longer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"And let me repeat what you saw last year."},{"time":53000,"text":"The bubbles are the countries."},{"time":54000,"text":"Here you have the fertility rate -- the number of children per woman --"},{"time":58000,"text":"and there you have the length of life in years."},{"time":62000,"text":"This is 1950 -- those were the industrialized countries,"},{"time":65000,"text":"those were developing countries."},{"time":66000,"text":"At that time there was a \"we\" and \"them.\""},{"time":68000,"text":"There was a huge difference in the world."},{"time":70000,"text":"But then it changed, and it went on quite well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"And this is what happens."},{"time":76000,"text":"You can see how China is the red, big bubble."},{"time":79000,"text":"The blue there is India."},{"time":80000,"text":"And they go over all this -- I'm going to try to be"},{"time":83000,"text":"a little more serious this year in showing you"},{"time":85000,"text":"how things really changed."},{"time":88000,"text":"And it's Africa that stands out as the problem down here, doesn't it?"},{"time":91000,"text":"Large families still, and the HIV epidemic"},{"time":94000,"text":"brought down the countries like this."},{"time":96000,"text":"This is more or less what we saw last year,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and this is how it will go on into the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102000,"text":"And I will talk on, is this possible?"},{"time":104000,"text":"Because you see now, I presented statistics that don't exist."},{"time":108000,"text":"Because this is where we are."},{"time":110000,"text":"Will it be possible that this will happen?"},{"time":114000,"text":"I cover my lifetime here, you know?"},{"time":116000,"text":"I expect to live 100 years."},{"time":118000,"text":"And this is where we are today."},{"time":120000,"text":"Now could we look here instead at the economic situation in the world?"},{"time":128000,"text":"And I would like to show that against child survival."},{"time":133000,"text":"We'll swap the axis."},{"time":135000,"text":"Here you have child mortality -- that is, survival --"},{"time":139000,"text":"four kids dying there, 200 dying there."},{"time":142000,"text":"And this is GDP per capita on this axis."},{"time":145000,"text":"And this was 2007."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"And if I go back in time, I've added some historical statistics --"},{"time":152000,"text":"here we go, here we go, here we go -- not so much statistics 100 years ago."},{"time":158000,"text":"Some countries still had statistics."},{"time":160000,"text":"We are looking down in the archive,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and when we are down into 1820,"},{"time":166000,"text":"there is only Austria and Sweden that can produce numbers."},{"time":170000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":173000,"text":"But they were down here. They had 1,000 dollars per person per year."},{"time":177000,"text":"And they lost one-fifth of their kids before their first birthday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"So this is what happens in the world, if we play the entire world."},{"time":184000,"text":"How they got slowly richer and richer,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and they add statistics."},{"time":188000,"text":"Isn't it beautiful when they get statistics?"},{"time":190000,"text":"You see the importance of that?"},{"time":192000,"text":"And here, children don't live longer."},{"time":194000,"text":"The last century, 1870, was bad for the kids in Europe,"},{"time":198000,"text":"because most of this statistics is Europe."},{"time":200000,"text":"It was only by the turn of the century"},{"time":203000,"text":"that more than 90 percent of the children survived their first year."},{"time":206000,"text":"This is India coming up, with the first data from India."},{"time":209000,"text":"And this is the United States moving away here, earning more money."},{"time":214000,"text":"And we will soon see China coming up in the very far end corner here."},{"time":219000,"text":"And it moves up with Mao Tse-Tung getting health,"},{"time":221000,"text":"not getting so rich."},{"time":222000,"text":"There he died, then Deng Xiaoping brings money."},{"time":225000,"text":"It moves this way over here."},{"time":227000,"text":"And the bubbles keep moving up there,"},{"time":229000,"text":"and this is what the world looks like today."},{"time":231000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"Let us have a look at the United States."},{"time":240000,"text":"We have a function here -- I can tell the world, \"Stay where you are.\""},{"time":244000,"text":"And I take the United States -- we still want to see the background --"},{"time":247000,"text":"I put them up like this, and now we go backwards."},{"time":250000,"text":"And we can see that the United States"},{"time":253000,"text":"goes to the right of the mainstream."},{"time":256000,"text":"They are on the money side all the time."},{"time":259000,"text":"And down in 1915, the United States was a neighbor of India --"},{"time":265000,"text":"present, contemporary India."},{"time":267000,"text":"And that means United States was richer,"},{"time":269000,"text":"but lost more kids than India is doing today, proportionally."},{"time":274000,"text":"And look here -- compare to the Philippines of today."},{"time":277000,"text":"The Philippines of today has almost the same economy"},{"time":281000,"text":"as the United States during the First World War."},{"time":283000,"text":"But we have to bring United States forward quite a while"},{"time":287000,"text":"to find the same health of the United States"},{"time":290000,"text":"as we have in the Philippines."},{"time":292000,"text":"About 1957 here, the health of the United States"},{"time":295000,"text":"is the same as the Philippines."},{"time":297000,"text":"And this is the drama of this world which many call globalized,"},{"time":300000,"text":"is that Asia, Arabic countries, Latin America,"},{"time":303000,"text":"are much more ahead in being healthy, educated,"},{"time":308000,"text":"having human resources than they are economically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"There's a discrepancy in what's happening today"},{"time":313000,"text":"in the emerging economies."},{"time":315000,"text":"There now, social benefits, social progress,"},{"time":319000,"text":"are going ahead of economical progress."},{"time":322000,"text":"And 1957 -- the United States had the same economy as Chile has today."},{"time":329000,"text":"And how long do we have to bring United States"},{"time":332000,"text":"to get the same health as Chile has today?"},{"time":335000,"text":"I think we have to go, there -- we have 2001, or 2002 --"},{"time":340000,"text":"the United States has the same health as Chile."},{"time":342000,"text":"Chile's catching up!"},{"time":344000,"text":"Within some years Chile may have better child survival"},{"time":346000,"text":"than the United States."},{"time":348000,"text":"This is really a change, that you have this lag"},{"time":351000,"text":"of more or less 30, 40 years' difference on the health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"And behind the health is the educational level."},{"time":358000,"text":"And there's a lot of infrastructure things,"},{"time":360000,"text":"and general human resources are there."},{"time":363000,"text":"Now we can take away this --"},{"time":366000,"text":"and I would like to show you the rate of speed,"},{"time":370000,"text":"the rate of change, how fast they have gone."},{"time":373000,"text":"And we go back to 1920, and I want to look at Japan."},{"time":381000,"text":"And I want to look at Sweden and the United States."},{"time":384000,"text":"And I'm going to stage a race here"},{"time":386000,"text":"between this sort of yellowish Ford here"},{"time":389000,"text":"and the red Toyota down there,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and the brownish Volvo."},{"time":393000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":395000,"text":"And here we go. Here we go."},{"time":397000,"text":"The Toyota has a very bad start down here, you can see,"},{"time":400000,"text":"and the United States Ford is going off-road there."},{"time":403000,"text":"And the Volvo is doing quite fine."},{"time":404000,"text":"This is the war. The Toyota got off track, and now"},{"time":406000,"text":"the Toyota is coming on the healthier side of Sweden --"},{"time":409000,"text":"can you see that?"},{"time":410000,"text":"And they are taking over Sweden,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and they are now healthier than Sweden."},{"time":413000,"text":"That's the part where I sold the Volvo and bought the Toyota."},{"time":415000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":418000,"text":"And now we can see that the rate of change was enormous in Japan."},{"time":422000,"text":"They really caught up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"And this changes gradually."},{"time":426000,"text":"We have to look over generations to understand it."},{"time":429000,"text":"And let me show you my own sort of family history --"},{"time":434000,"text":"we made these graphs here."},{"time":436000,"text":"And this is the same thing, money down there, and health, you know?"},{"time":440000,"text":"And this is my family."},{"time":443000,"text":"This is Sweden, 1830, when my great-great-grandma was born."},{"time":448000,"text":"Sweden was like Sierra Leone today."},{"time":451000,"text":"And this is when great-grandma was born, 1863."},{"time":455000,"text":"And Sweden was like Mozambique."},{"time":457000,"text":"And this is when my grandma was born, 1891."},{"time":459000,"text":"She took care of me as a child,"},{"time":461000,"text":"so I'm not talking about statistic now --"},{"time":463000,"text":"now it's oral history in my family."},{"time":466000,"text":"That's when I believe statistics,"},{"time":467000,"text":"when it's grandma-verified statistics."},{"time":470000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":473000,"text":"I think it's the best way of verifying historical statistics."},{"time":476000,"text":"Sweden was like Ghana."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's interesting to see the enormous diversity"},{"time":480000,"text":"within sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":483000,"text":"I told you last year, I'll tell you again,"},{"time":485000,"text":"my mother was born in Egypt, and I -- who am I?"},{"time":488000,"text":"I'm the Mexican in the family."},{"time":490000,"text":"And my daughter, she was born in Chile,"},{"time":492000,"text":"and the grand-daughter was born in Singapore,"},{"time":494000,"text":"now the healthiest country on this Earth."},{"time":496000,"text":"It bypassed Sweden about two to three years ago,"},{"time":498000,"text":"with better child survival."},{"time":500000,"text":"But they're very small, you know?"},{"time":501000,"text":"They're so close to the hospital we can never"},{"time":503000,"text":"beat them out in these forests."},{"time":504000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":507000,"text":"But homage to Singapore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"Singapore is the best one."},{"time":510000,"text":"Now this looks also like a very good story."},{"time":514000,"text":"But it's not really that easy, that it's all a good story."},{"time":518000,"text":"Because I have to show you one of the other facilities."},{"time":521000,"text":"We can also make the color here represent the variable --"},{"time":526000,"text":"and what am I choosing here?"},{"time":527000,"text":"Carbon-dioxide emission, metric ton per capita."},{"time":532000,"text":"This is 1962, and United States was emitting 16 tons per person."},{"time":537000,"text":"And China was emitting 0.6,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and India was emitting 0.32 tons per capita."},{"time":543000,"text":"And what happens when we moved on?"},{"time":546000,"text":"Well, you see the nice story of getting richer"},{"time":548000,"text":"and getting healthier --"},{"time":549000,"text":"everyone did it at the cost of emission of carbon dioxide."},{"time":554000,"text":"There is no one who has done it so far."},{"time":557000,"text":"And we don't have all the updated data"},{"time":560000,"text":"any longer, because this is really hot data today."},{"time":563000,"text":"And there we are, 2001."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566000,"text":"And in the discussion I attended with global leaders, you know,"},{"time":570000,"text":"many say now the problem is that the emerging economies,"},{"time":574000,"text":"they are getting out too much carbon dioxide."},{"time":577000,"text":"The Minister of the Environment of India said,"},{"time":579000,"text":"\"Well, you were the one who caused the problem.\""},{"time":582000,"text":"The OECD countries -- the high-income countries --"},{"time":585000,"text":"they were the ones who caused the climate change."},{"time":588000,"text":"\"But we forgive you, because you didn't know it."},{"time":590000,"text":"But from now on, we count per capita."},{"time":593000,"text":"From now on we count per capita."},{"time":595000,"text":"And everyone is responsible for the per capita emission.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"This really shows you, we have not seen good economic"},{"time":601000,"text":"and health progress anywhere in the world"},{"time":603000,"text":"without destroying the climate."},{"time":608000,"text":"And this is really what has to be changed."},{"time":611000,"text":"I've been criticized for showing you a too positive image of the world,"},{"time":614000,"text":"but I don't think it's like this."},{"time":616000,"text":"The world is quite a messy place."},{"time":618000,"text":"This we can call Dollar Street."},{"time":620000,"text":"Everyone lives on this street here."},{"time":622000,"text":"What they earn here -- what number they live on --"},{"time":625000,"text":"is how much they earn per day."},{"time":626000,"text":"This family earns about one dollar per day."},{"time":630000,"text":"We drive up the street here,"},{"time":631000,"text":"we find a family here which earns about two to three dollars a day."},{"time":635000,"text":"And we drive away here -- we find the first garden in the street,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and they earn 10 to 50 dollars a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"And how do they live?"},{"time":642000,"text":"If we look at the bed here, we can see"},{"time":645000,"text":"that they sleep on a rug on the floor."},{"time":648000,"text":"This is what poverty line is --"},{"time":650000,"text":"80 percent of the family income is just to cover the energy needs,"},{"time":653000,"text":"the food for the day."},{"time":655000,"text":"This is two to five dollars. You have a bed."},{"time":658000,"text":"And here it's a much nicer bedroom, you can see."},{"time":661000,"text":"I lectured on this for Ikea, and they wanted to see"},{"time":663000,"text":"the sofa immediately here."},{"time":665000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":667000,"text":"And this is the sofa, how it will emerge from there."},{"time":671000,"text":"And the interesting thing, when you go around here in the photo panorama,"},{"time":674000,"text":"you see the family still sitting on the floor there."},{"time":676000,"text":"Although there is a sofa,"},{"time":678000,"text":"if you watch in the kitchen, you can see that"},{"time":680000,"text":"the great difference for women does not come between one to 10 dollars."},{"time":685000,"text":"It comes beyond here, when you really can get"},{"time":687000,"text":"good working conditions in the family."},{"time":690000,"text":"And if you really want to see the difference,"},{"time":692000,"text":"you look at the toilet over here."},{"time":694000,"text":"This can change. This can change."},{"time":696000,"text":"These are all pictures and images from Africa,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and it can become much better."},{"time":702000,"text":"We can get out of poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"My own research has not been in IT or anything like this."},{"time":707000,"text":"I spent 20 years in interviews with African farmers"},{"time":710000,"text":"who were on the verge of famine."},{"time":713000,"text":"And this is the result of the farmers-needs research."},{"time":715000,"text":"The nice thing here is that you can't see"},{"time":717000,"text":"who are the researchers in this picture."},{"time":719000,"text":"That's when research functions in poor societies --"},{"time":722000,"text":"you must really live with the people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"When you're in poverty, everything is about survival."},{"time":730000,"text":"It's about having food."},{"time":732000,"text":"And these two young farmers, they are girls now --"},{"time":734000,"text":"because the parents are dead from HIV and AIDS --"},{"time":738000,"text":"they discuss with a trained agronomist."},{"time":740000,"text":"This is one of the best agronomists in Malawi, Junatambe Kumbira,"},{"time":744000,"text":"and he's discussing what sort of cassava they will plant --"},{"time":746000,"text":"the best converter of sunshine to food that man has found."},{"time":750000,"text":"And they are very, very eagerly interested to get advice,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and that's to survive in poverty."},{"time":756000,"text":"That's one context."},{"time":757000,"text":"Getting out of poverty."},{"time":759000,"text":"The women told us one thing. \"Get us technology."},{"time":762000,"text":"We hate this mortar, to stand hours and hours."},{"time":765000,"text":"Get us a mill so that we can mill our flour,"},{"time":768000,"text":"then we will be able to pay for the rest ourselves.\""},{"time":771000,"text":"Technology will bring you out of poverty,"},{"time":774000,"text":"but there's a need for a market to get away from poverty."},{"time":778000,"text":"And this woman is very happy now, bringing her products to the market."},{"time":781000,"text":"But she's very thankful for the public investment in schooling"},{"time":783000,"text":"so she can count, and won't be cheated when she reaches the market."},{"time":786000,"text":"She wants her kid to be healthy, so she can go to the market"},{"time":789000,"text":"and doesn't have to stay home."},{"time":791000,"text":"And she wants the infrastructure -- it is nice with a paved road."},{"time":794000,"text":"It's also good with credit."},{"time":796000,"text":"Micro-credits gave her the bicycle, you know."},{"time":799000,"text":"And information will tell her when to go to market with which product."},{"time":802000,"text":"You can do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"I find my experience from 20 years of Africa is that"},{"time":807000,"text":"the seemingly impossible is possible."},{"time":810000,"text":"Africa has not done bad."},{"time":812000,"text":"In 50 years they've gone from a pre-Medieval situation"},{"time":815000,"text":"to a very decent 100-year-ago Europe,"},{"time":818000,"text":"with a functioning nation and state."},{"time":821000,"text":"I would say that sub-Saharan Africa has done best in the world"},{"time":824000,"text":"during the last 50 years."},{"time":825000,"text":"Because we don't consider where they came from."},{"time":827000,"text":"It's this stupid concept of developing countries"},{"time":830000,"text":"that puts us, Argentina and Mozambique together 50 years ago,"},{"time":833000,"text":"and says that Mozambique did worse."},{"time":836000,"text":"We have to know a little more about the world."},{"time":838000,"text":"I have a neighbor who knows 200 types of wine."},{"time":841000,"text":"He knows everything."},{"time":842000,"text":"He knows the name of the grape, the temperature and everything."},{"time":844000,"text":"I only know two types of wine -- red and white."},{"time":847000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":849000,"text":"But my neighbor only knows two types of countries --"},{"time":851000,"text":"industrialized and developing."},{"time":853000,"text":"And I know 200, I know about the small data."},{"time":856000,"text":"But you can do that."},{"time":857000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862000,"text":"But I have to get serious. And how do you get serious?"},{"time":864000,"text":"You make a PowerPoint, you know?"},{"time":866000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":871000,"text":"Homage to the Office package, no?"},{"time":875000,"text":"What is this, what is this, what am I telling?"},{"time":877000,"text":"I'm telling you that there are many dimensions of development."},{"time":880000,"text":"Everyone wants your pet thing."},{"time":882000,"text":"If you are in the corporate sector, you love micro-credit."},{"time":885000,"text":"If you are fighting in a non-governmental organization,"},{"time":887000,"text":"you love equity between gender."},{"time":890000,"text":"Or if you are a teacher, you'll love UNESCO, and so on."},{"time":892000,"text":"On the global level, we have to have more than our own thing."},{"time":894000,"text":"We need everything."},{"time":896000,"text":"All these things are important for development,"},{"time":898000,"text":"especially when you just get out of poverty"},{"time":900000,"text":"and you should go towards welfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"Now, what we need to think about"},{"time":905000,"text":"is, what is a goal for development,"},{"time":908000,"text":"and what are the means for development?"},{"time":909000,"text":"Let me first grade what are the most important means."},{"time":913000,"text":"Economic growth to me, as a public-health professor,"},{"time":915000,"text":"is the most important thing for development"},{"time":919000,"text":"because it explains 80 percent of survival."},{"time":922000,"text":"Governance. To have a government which functions --"},{"time":925000,"text":"that's what brought California out of the misery of 1850."},{"time":929000,"text":"It was the government that made law function finally."},{"time":933000,"text":"Education, human resources are important."},{"time":935000,"text":"Health is also important, but not that much as a mean."},{"time":939000,"text":"Environment is important."},{"time":941000,"text":"Human rights is also important, but it just gets one cross."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"Now what about goals? Where are we going toward?"},{"time":946000,"text":"We are not interested in money."},{"time":948000,"text":"Money is not a goal."},{"time":949000,"text":"It's the best mean, but I give it zero as a goal."},{"time":953000,"text":"Governance, well it's fun to vote in a little thing,"},{"time":956000,"text":"but it's not a goal."},{"time":958000,"text":"And going to school, that's not a goal, it's a mean."},{"time":962000,"text":"Health I give two points. I mean it's nice to be healthy"},{"time":964000,"text":"-- at my age especially -- you can stand here, you're healthy."},{"time":966000,"text":"And that's good, it gets two plusses."},{"time":968000,"text":"Environment is very, very crucial."},{"time":970000,"text":"There's nothing for the grandkid if you don't save up."},{"time":972000,"text":"But where are the important goals?"},{"time":974000,"text":"Of course, it's human rights."},{"time":976000,"text":"Human rights is the goal,"},{"time":978000,"text":"but it's not that strong of a mean for achieving development."},{"time":982000,"text":"And culture. Culture is the most important thing, I would say,"},{"time":986000,"text":"because that's what brings joy to life."},{"time":988000,"text":"That's the value of living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":990000,"text":"So the seemingly impossible is possible."},{"time":993000,"text":"Even African countries can achieve this."},{"time":996000,"text":"And I've shown you the shot where the seemingly impossible is possible."},{"time":1002000,"text":"And remember, please remember my main message,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"which is this: the seemingly impossible is possible."},{"time":1009000,"text":"We can have a good world."},{"time":1011000,"text":"I showed you the shots, I proved it in the PowerPoint,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and I think I will convince you also by culture."},{"time":1020000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1024000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1025000,"text":"Bring me my sword!"},{"time":1031000,"text":"Sword swallowing is from ancient India."},{"time":1036000,"text":"It's a cultural expression that for thousands of years"},{"time":1041000,"text":"has inspired human beings to think beyond the obvious."},{"time":1047000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1049000,"text":"And I will now prove to you that the seemingly impossible is possible"},{"time":1054000,"text":"by taking this piece of steel -- solid steel --"},{"time":1058000,"text":"this is the army bayonet from the Swedish Army, 1850,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"in the last year we had war."},{"time":1064000,"text":"And it's all solid steel -- you can hear here."},{"time":1067000,"text":"And I'm going to take this blade of steel,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"and push it down through my body of blood and flesh,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"and prove to you that the seemingly impossible is possible."},{"time":1083000,"text":"Can I request a moment of absolute silence?"},{"time":1098000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}